@Professoriz 

The most simple way to explain false positives is seeing it like this:

If you've lost the key of your house you can do a few things, like:

1. Call the police to break into your house legally.
2. Call a burglar to break into your house illegally.

Both do the same, but only the police has official permission and legal tools. 


In a way each crack is a virus, cause it has been modified or modifies the system without official permission or tools.
Only bad viruses will cause harm to the system, while good viruses break "into the system" without causing any harm.
So there are good and bad viruses, and antivirus software doesn't make a difference between good and bad viruses.
Besides antivirus software there are many options to check what a crack does, and if it's causing any harm.
